page.title: 18TRANSPORT,KINNERTON EVENJOBB
page.content: TRAFFIC SURVEY-THURSDAY,JUNE 27th,1985 3 p.m. to 3.3O p.m. AT KINNERTON. 3 CARS, 2 LAND ROVERS, 1 LORRY WENT NORTH TOWARDS CASCOB.1 BICYCLE,3 CARS 1 TRACTOR,2 LORRIES WENT SOUTH TOWARDS WALTON.1 BUS TRAVELLED EAST PLUS 22 CARS, 4 TRACTORS,6 VANS & 2 LORRIES TOWARDS BEGGAR'S BUSH ON B4372.1 MOTOR BIKE,6 CARS & 4 LAND ROVERS WENT WEST ON B4372 TOWARDS NEW RADNOR. TRAFFIC SURVEY-TUESDAY,JULY 2nd,1985 2.2O-2.5O p.m.AT EVENJOBB. 7 CARS,1 BUS,1 LAND ROVER & 1 VAN WENT NORTH TOWARDS BEGGAR'S BUSH.6 CARS,1 MOTOR BIKE,1 LAND ROVER & 1 LORRY WENT SOUTH TOWARDS WALTON.7 CARS,1 LORRY & 1 VAN TRAVELLED EAST TOWARDS PRESTEIGNE.2 CARS TRAVELLED WEST THROUGH EVENJOBB TOWARDS KINNERTON.
